<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">To help you out, a 56k modem can only connect at a maximum of 53k, no matter what anyone tells you or what AOL spitts out. The FCC and the phone companies have an agreement that is the max allowed. However, how fast you can connect depends upon your phone line. The phone company only guarantees 9600 baud (9.6k). The best I have ever seen was about 5.1k at my friends house. He lives across the street from a phone router station.</FONT>
</TD></TR>

